---
title: BeaconLink Plugin Loading Sequence
---

sequenceDiagram
    autonumber

    participant Control as BeaconLink Control Plane
    participant PluginMgr as Plugin Manager
    participant Registry as Plugin Registry
    participant Policy as Policy Engine
    participant Catalog as Capability Catalog
    participant Runtime as Runtime Manager
    participant Plugin as Runtime Plugin
    participant Adapter as Runtime Adapter
    participant Events as Event Streaming Platform
    participant Audit as Audit Service

    %% =====================================================
    %% Platform Startup
    %% =====================================================

    Note over Control,PluginMgr: BeaconLink services initialize<br/>during platform startup

    Control->>PluginMgr: Initialize plugin framework

    PluginMgr->>Registry: Discover installed plugins
    Registry-->>PluginMgr: Available plugin metadata

    %% =====================================================
    %% Plugin Discovery
    %% =====================================================

    loop For Each Registered Plugin

        PluginMgr->>Registry: Load plugin manifest

        Registry-->>PluginMgr: Manifest

        Note right of Registry: Manifest includes:<br/>• Plugin ID<br/>• Version<br/>• Capabilities<br/>• Dependencies<br/>• Compatibility<br/>• Signature

        PluginMgr->>PluginMgr: Validate manifest

    end

    %% =====================================================
    %% Trust Verification
    %% =====================================================

    loop For Each Plugin

        PluginMgr->>Policy: Verify plugin policy

        Policy->>Policy: Validate signature
        Policy->>Policy: Validate compatibility
        Policy->>Policy: Validate permissions

        alt Plugin Trusted

            Policy-->>PluginMgr: Approved

        else Plugin Rejected

            Policy-->>PluginMgr: Rejected

            PluginMgr->>Audit: Record plugin rejection

            PluginMgr->>Events: Publish PluginRejected

        end

    end

    %% =====================================================
    %% Dependency Resolution
    %% =====================================================

    PluginMgr->>PluginMgr: Resolve dependencies

    PluginMgr->>Registry: Load dependency graph

    Registry-->>PluginMgr: Dependency information

    PluginMgr->>PluginMgr: Determine load order

    %% =====================================================
    %% Plugin Initialization
    %% =====================================================

    loop Load Approved Plugins

        PluginMgr->>Plugin: Initialize plugin

        Plugin->>Plugin: Allocate resources
        Plugin->>Plugin: Register services

        Plugin->>Runtime: Register runtime adapter

        Runtime->>Adapter: Activate adapter

        Adapter-->>Runtime: Adapter initialized

        Runtime-->>Plugin: Registration successful

    end

    %% =====================================================
    %% Capability Registration
    %% =====================================================

    PluginMgr->>Catalog: Register plugin capabilities

    Catalog->>Catalog: Update capability index

    Catalog-->>PluginMgr: Capabilities published

    PluginMgr->>Events: Publish PluginLoaded

    PluginMgr->>Audit: Record successful initialization

    %% =====================================================
    %% Runtime Availability
    %% =====================================================

    Control->>Runtime: Query available runtimes

    Runtime-->>Control: Supported runtime list

    Note over Runtime,Control: Examples:<br/>• Kubernetes<br/>• Docker<br/>• Nomad<br/>• Virtual Machines<br/>• Serverless<br/>• Custom Plugins

    %% =====================================================
    %% Health Monitoring
    %% =====================================================

    loop Continuous Plugin Monitoring

        PluginMgr->>Plugin: Health check

        Plugin-->>PluginMgr: Status

        alt Plugin Healthy

            PluginMgr->>Catalog: Refresh capability state

        else Plugin Failure

            PluginMgr->>Runtime: Disable adapter

            Runtime-->>PluginMgr: Adapter disabled

            PluginMgr->>Events: Publish PluginUnloaded

            PluginMgr->>Audit: Record plugin failure

        end

    end

    %% =====================================================
    %% Hot Reload
    %% =====================================================

    opt Plugin Upgrade or Installation

        Registry->>PluginMgr: New plugin available

        PluginMgr->>Policy: Validate updated plugin

        Policy-->>PluginMgr: Approved

        PluginMgr->>Plugin: Graceful shutdown

        Plugin->>Plugin: Release resources

        PluginMgr->>Plugin: Load updated version

        Plugin->>Runtime: Register new adapter

        Runtime-->>PluginMgr: Upgrade complete

        PluginMgr->>Events: Publish PluginReloaded

    end

    Note over PluginMgr,Runtime: BeaconLink dynamically discovers,<br/>validates, loads, monitors, and reloads plugins<br/>without modifying the core platform architecture.